steadfast /ˈstɛdfəst/

1. ADJ If someone is steadfast in something that they are doing, they are convinced that what they are doing is right and they refuse to change it or to give up. 坚定的 

例： He remained steadfast in his belief that he had done the right thing. 他仍然坚信自己做了正确的事情。

